{
  "texts": [
    "As a result of Step 1-3, a service data model containing the name and description of the desired service is obtained.In summary, these three steps allow for the extraction of user needs related to new services and the acquisition of service overviews.",
    "(A2) Acquisition of upcycling cases that can satisfy those needsBy utilizing the SUCCEED system from prior research, we acquire insights useful for developing services that fulfill needs identified in (A1).",
    "The process of acquiring these insights is illustrated in Fig. 8 and is conducted in the following two steps:• Step 2-1: Extract keywords that represent the needs;• Step 2-2: Search for upcycling cases using the keywords.In step 2-1, we extract keywords that accurately represent user needs.",
    "In the 6W1H needs data model, each element of 6W1H is expressed in sentences rather than words, rendering the search function of the SUCCEED system inapplicable in its current form.",
    "It is necessary to extract several distinctive keywords."
  ]
}